SIMPLE: happily
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Happily
<hw>Hap"pi*ly</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧p"p⟦icr⟧*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<ety>[From <er>Happy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>By chance;
peradventure; haply.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Piers
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By good fortune; fortunately; luckily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Preferred by conquest, <qex>happily</qex> o'erthrown.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In a happy manner or state; in happy circumstances;
<as>as, he lived <ex>happily</ex> with his wife</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>With address or dexterity; gracefully; felicitously;
in a manner to insure success; with success.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Formed by thy converse, <qex>happily</qex> to steer⟦br⟧
From grave to gay, from lively to severe.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Fortunately; luckily; successfully; prosperously;
contentedly; dexterously; felicitously.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Happiness</ent>⟦br⟧
